The deck uses the “Maliss” monster lineup to rapidly build a strong board of Link monsters (especially Cyberse ones via the @Ignister engine) while banishing “Maliss” cards to unlock powerful effects. You start by summoning low-level Maliss monsters (like March Hare, White Rabbit, Dormouse, Chessy Cat) to set or banish cards, then leverage the @Ignister cards (such as Backup @Ignister, Wizard @Ignister) to fetch monsters and trigger Link Summons. Once you’ve established one of your Maliss Link monsters (like Hearts Crypter, White Binder, Red Ransom) alongside generic Link bosses (like Accesscode Talker or Firewall Dragon), you control the field by both disruption (through trap/banish effects) and board presence. The “Maliss in Underground” field spell helps by making your Maliss Link monsters extremely strong when you’ve banished several Maliss traps, while also forcing your opponent’s monsters to target your Maliss Links letting you funnel attacks and protect your other cards. In short: banish Maliss cards summon Maliss links overlay with @Ignister support lock the opponent out of plays with disruption and banish-effects.
version 1.0 of Tri-Brigade using the Radiant Typhoon Engine to accelerate Link Climbing.

This version of Branded is looking to set up an endbaord with a Dragon Lock for on field effects and a Mirrorjade on the next turn. Other tech pieces in this list include a small Shaddoll package to enhance our boardbreaking and consistency with High Spirits (we can also run a fun card in side deck), a proper Dogmatika package is here to really make use of Fallen&Virtuous multiple times in a grind game. A card normally not that good in branded is also making a name for itself as an alternate to non-fuisonable bosses on our opponent's field: The Bystial Aluber becomes really powerful if your opponent only has dragons due to buster dragon's effect as he's just a "quick-play"change of heart we can access through engine. IDP with our end board is criminal btw, may consider a 3rd copy.

For the side deck I'm currently testing some options to see what I like most. Extra copies of Thunderbolt make it more likley to interrupt combos when going 2nd with our busted Fallen&Virtuous. I've also added Shaddoll Fusion for when we're forced to go 2nd as Construct is uniquley powerful into extra deck end boards and forces the fusion to be negated or we shatter their board with a free +1.

deck_excerpt: Burn bright under the light of the fae!
deck_description: First attempt at a Domain Format deck!

Despite the Diabellstar/Azamina engine being far too pricey to run alongside everything else, this deck surprisingly runs very efficiently like 95% of the time. Piri Reis Map to search Astellar of the White Forest, which is basically your best starter. Astellar alongside Toy Box allows you to perform cold fusion essentially, especially since it allows Toy Soldier to search for Rucia of the White Forest to leave your normal search via Tales of the White Forest for something actually good like Elzette. 

Deck Breakdown (I am not a professional):

MAIN DECK:

3x Astellar: Excellent starter, almost always summoning Silvy, plus it summons itself back after you summon Rciela to make an easy Diabell (or Amritara if you already made her). Piri Reis Map at max copies to find her as soon as possible.

3x Silvy of the White Forest: Can also be a great starter if you didnt open a way to Astellar. Almost always searching Tales, or Witch of the White Forest if you already have Tales, or Scourge, if you already have those 2, or Woes if ok I think you get the point.

2x Elzette of the White Forest: A nice extender, a good search off of Witch or Tales, or if you open Toy Box or Toy Soldier, even a starter, since it searches Astellar. But not that good, so you only run 3 copies, don't wanna be bricked up on her

1x Elzette, Azamina of the White Forest: The cooler, more advanced version. That's why it costs 22 points. It can summon literally any White Forest from your hand, and when you inevitably synch it off the field, it can search ANY Sinful Spoil card (hint hint Vengeance hint hint). Or Subversion if you side into it. Great card honestly, unfortunately the fusions are too expensive to run alongside her (RIP Azamina engine)

1x Rucia of the White Forest: It's just an extender. It also helps the synchros dodge targetted effects alongside Silvy. Oh, it nets an extra draw. Thats it, not really much to say here.

3x Toy Box: Fuels all the White Forest effects, and also makes the battle phase dangerous with its secret 2nd effect most people tend to forget about. Running max copies for obvious reasons, you wanna see this card.

3x Toy Soldier: The favourite child of the Toy Box engine. By itself can search Toy Box for more fuel for the White Forest cards, and somehow even better if Toy Box is already on the field because it can search any lvl 4 LIGHT monster (Centur-ion was too expensive, why is Auxila 33 points?) Max copies for obvious reasons.

1x Toy Tank: The less loved child of the Toy Box engine, but don't worry. I love you. It's an extra body on board if you wanna synchro directly to 12, and if needed can tribute itself to unbrick your hand. Not as versatile as Soldier though, but can be searched and constantly recursed by Toy Box so you really only need 1 copy anyway.

1x Diabellze the White Witch: (This card is always treated as a "White Forest" card) AND THANK GOD. Very easy to search, very easy to summon, protects all your monsters if you control Vengeance or Queen, and you're always dumping Curse of Diabell with its effect, unless you wanna flex on your opponent and dump Vengeance to waste your and your opponent's time... or you already drew Filia and you dont need to use it

1x Diabellstar Vengeance: Beauty. Grace. A single target pop and a conditional synchro tuner summon, all for the low low price of half your lifepoints. Steep cost, but the only lifepoint that matters is the very last one, so who cares. Easily searchable off of Filia or cooler Elzette, can summon from GY too, so destroying it does nothing for your opponent (unless you run out of traps to banish lol)

3x Tales of the White Forest: Main searcher. Fuel for the Forests. Can pitch off of Astellar, set itself back, send for Rciela, then get it back with Queen and search for Diabellze or Elzette... or Rucia I guess... 

1x Witch of the White Forest: Second best searcher after Tales, but 33 points holy hell! At least now you don't have to worry about locking yourself out of your Azaminas if you use it to search a starter (I miss them). Plus it turns your lvl 2's into tuners so you can jump to Chengying (Chaos Angel too expensive) or Poplar if needs be (Just ignore the dark Satellite Warrior in the extra deck for now, thanks). And after it's served its purpose it can simply be sent as fuel for the Forests. Lovely card.

1x Scourge of the White Forest: I had 1 card slot left to fill and after perusing all the possible white forest and sinful spoils I could splash in, Scourge beat out Morrian because it can be used turn one. Plus a negate that can recover Diabellze/Queen/Poplar/cooler Elzette sounded too good to pass up. Your White Forest synchros are all easily recoverable due to Silvy and Rucia anyway.

1x Filia Diabell: It has one purpose, which after it fulfills, it becomes useless. No need to run more than one. Easily searchable off of Curse, which is easily searchable off of Diabellze, which is easily searchable off of any of the 20 million White Forest searchers. It's purpose is to search Vengeance then be banished forever. +500 atk also nice.

1x Curse of Diabell: It has one purpose, which after it fulfills, it becomes useless. No need to run more than one. Easily searchable off of Diabellze, which is easily searchable off of any of the 20 million White Forest searchers. It's purpose is to search Filia Diabell then be banished forever. Fuel for the Forests.

1x Woes of the White Forest: Only one copy, but thats all you need, can be searched off of Silvy or Rciela if you really need it. Fuel for the Forests, which can then come back to summon ANY White Forest monster from Hand or Deck, after which you can quick synchro into any White Forest synchro (Its Silvera if you're curious). Unlike Morrian, which is a Book of Moon, Woes is effectively a Book of Eclipse without the drawing. You can also get Queen if needs be to stagnate the Silvera summon to a more opportune time.

Non-Engine Time!

3x Piri Reis Map: It gets Astellar, what more do you want me to say? Drew it and a copy of Astellar in your opener? Congrats you don't need to pay half your LP and it can be fuel for Astellar. Necessary consistency piece, tried the deck without it, because I'm not fond of paying half my LP twice, but kept bricking like crazy. Load bearing card.

3x Ultimate Slayer: Genesys staple. Honestly such a good card, I thank the TCG devs that they didn't point this card. Garura, Malong, and Aggregator will always find a place in my deck. Heads up, Enigmaster Packbit unfortunately does not trigger your Forest Spell/Trap on either effect, and your extra is tight enough, don't fall for the bait.

3x Book of Eclipse: I had 20 points left over after adding all my necessary engine cards, and was debating between Ghost Belle, Ghost Ogre, Droll, and Nibiru. But after testing they bricked like hell. This card can become Fuel for the Forests if needs be, plus it and Silvera being used on the same turn can cause people to ragequit. I'm aware I can drop this and play Chaos Angel in the extra, but this adds needed power in the main deck without compromising consistency or reliability.

3x Skull Meister: Genesys staple. GY effects are very common and this is free, so why not. Plus, can be used as a lvl 4 for sycnhro purposes if you're really down bad.

1x Mannadium Reframing: Omni negate counter trap. Searchable off of Amritara. All it needs is for you to control a Synchro. Easy addition to the deck.

EXTRA DECK:

Rciela, Sinister Soul of the White Forest: Main combo piece. Basically what you go for first almost all the time. Gets any White Forest spell you need at the time and can be used to go for Queen. Also underrated, it can search ANY LIGHT SPELLCASTER (dear god why is Centur-ion so expensive). Can be bounced by Silvy and Rucia from field or GY. Good card.

Silvera, Wolf Tamer of the White Forest: I heard you like Book of Eclipse. Can be summoned Queen or Woes on your opponent's turn. Also has the added effect of adding +500 atk to your Illusion and Spellcaster synchros, and secret effect, makes them become Chaos MAX with double piercing. Oh did I mention that Silvera's book of eclipse effect isn't once per turn? You can bounce it back with Silvy and Rucia and summon it again. Isn't that funny?

Diabell, Queen of the White Forest: The White Forest "Boss Monster". Recovers any spell on summon, and can summon your tuner synchro on your opponent's turn from basically anywhere. You're mainly summoning Silvera because Book of Eclipse on legs is very strong, but on occassion summons Poplar and Zapper Shrimp, both of which can quick synchro. Can be used as synchro material and recovered via Rucia and Silvy, then summoned again to set up. Honestly such a good card, I see why it costs 25 points. Just remember you need to summon it with a synchro tuner specifically to return a spell from GY.

Poplar of the White Forest: We have Poplar at home! Jokes aside, while you dont often go for this one, it can definitely come up. Summon it on your opponent's turn to quick synchro into Legatia or Vengeance Dragon, or even Silvera if you have a stray lvl 2 on field, because everyone loves Book of Eclipse. Plus, on your turn you can set up your cards to summon Doom Dragon for board breaking purposes. He's no Snake-Eyes Poplar but he still does a good job.

Snake-Eyes Vengeance Dragon: According to lore, this is Poplar's final form. And yeah this guy's GOOD. It does what Sinful Spoils of Subversion - Snake-Eye does but as a quick effect, then can pop 2 cards during the Battle Phase. Only drawback is that it has the Mirrorjade condition, where you can't use the Subversion effect again during the next turn. Still a very solid card, and your go-to lvl 12.

Snake-Eyes Doomed Dragon: I genuinely have no clue where this card fits in the lore. Anyway, its also Subversion on summon. The only way to really summon it though is via Poplar set up, after which it's used as synchro material for Vegenace Dragon. Still an include though, that's still very good.

Visas Amritara: It searches Mannadium Reframing. Anything else it does is just a plus. It can pop one of your own monsters to free up space, and also give an atk boost to Synchros, and makes Reframing destroy the card it negates if it's still face up when on the field. Your go to lvl 8 after getting Queen set up (unless you drew Reframing).

Zapper Shrimp: Queen can summon it and it not only pops a spell/trap, but triggers your Toy Box engine. Plus it's perfectly suited for quick synchros into your lvl 10's (or on occassion your 12's).

Tri-Edge Master: During testing of this deck, there is a 1 in 1000 chance that you end up in a scenario where you would end up with too many Tuners and you need just one lvl 6 non-tuner synchro to unlock everything. Every time I thought this card was useless and took it out, that scenario came up again and I regret it. Swap him for a more useful monster if you wish, but watch out!

Centur-Ion Legatia: Generic lvl 12 synchro that draws a card and pops a monster on summon. Protects your weaker monsters from battle and has a whopping 3500 atk stat. Great quick synchro target.

Swordsoul Supreme Sovereign - Chengying: Generic lvl 10 that's just very good all-round. Buffs itself, lowers your opponent's atk stats, protects itself and banishes 2 of your opponent's cards when anything is banished? Easy include (If Chaos Angel didn't cost 20 points, he would be here instead).

Satellite Warrior: Th elephant in the room. Yes, he's dark attribute. Yes, he conflicts with Witch of the White Forest. But only on your turn. He makes for a perfect quick synchro target when mass removal is needed. Plus he becomes BIG if he pops anything. +1000 atk for each card destroyed gets a little nutty.

Garura, Wings of Resonant Life: Ultimate Slayer tax. Plus a draw one is neat.

Mereologic Aggregator: Ultimate Slayer tax. Plus a targeted negate is neat.

Golden Cloud Beast - Malong: Ultimate Slayer tax. Plus a bounce is neat. Wait... What's this? We're getting reports that this card can actually be used in this deck offensively? Oh wow yeah, it can. You can summon it and use it as a bridge to Queen or Amritara and still get it's bounce effect. Okay that's pretty neat ngl. And it triggers Queen because its a synchro tuner!

The Side Deck is whatever fits your needs at the time, I think Subversion is funny. Have fun! (And if you read this far, thanks for taking the time out)

deck_excerpt: Infinite gas. You WILL summon Psy-Reflector!
deck_description:
A fairly straight foward Assault Mode deck without all the new OCG only cards for obvious reasons. I chose the Psychic cards to pair with the strategy because Psy-Reflector is also a Psychic monster, so you get some needed extra bridges into it, and being able to play P.U.N.K.s is also pretty nice.

The deck has all sorts of ways to get Teleport, you can use it as a starter, extender or even as an interruption putting it face-down and getting Ghost Ogre at the start of your opponent's turn.

Beware of some locks, though. Serene Psychic Girl locks you into summoning Psychics from your Extra Deck for the rest of the turn, so you want to summon Stardust before commiting into her. In general, reading your cards is good.

The side deck Winged Dragon of Ra is a meme, you don't have to use it, but it's just too funny.

deck_excerpt: Casual deck build around Divine Dragon Lord Felgrand.
deck_description: Casual deck build around Divine Dragon Lord Felgrand.

My Spright Adventure brew for Genesys 

water enchantress + nimble angler is what you love to see

Any way to get 2 lvl 2s on board is combo, which ends with 2 interruptions (usually double cross+playhouse), depending on what you have you can extend further

melffy cathy is an interruption by itself which is why i play 3, you also search it instead of playhouse if you happen to draw playhouse

also if youre facing an empty board 2 level 2s allow you to otk: make gigantic- special blue - add jet - add gamma burst - activate gamma burst and attack with all 3 for 8200 damage, i sucks that we can only play 1 gigantic but it is what it is, if your opponent has dark monsters in grave number 29 can act as a pseudo second gigantic

Post side the shaddoll package can come in to either help you grind with golden lord (you can send dracoback from field and reequip it for free) but you dont have to play him if you dont want to, but its mostly there to access your engine by sending nimble angler from deck which specials 2 level 2s from deck

the paleo stuff is for more going first power and double as level 2 bodies since youre always going to have traps to make them comeback from grave

a cool play you can make going second if you have dinomischus in hand and a way to make a rank 2+nimble angler in hand is: make opabinia which allows you to activate dinomischus from hand and discarding nimble angler to special 2 level 2s (if it doesnt get negated)

The deck isnt meta but its very fun to play

deck_excerpt: Adventure and Medius as starters to reduce reliance on normal summons.
deck_description:
Optimal Combo:

Medius the Pure  in hand and Adventure engine -> Discard Medius the Pure  for Adventure engine and summon wandering Wandering Gryphon Rider . Special Medius the Pure by shuffling a monster from deck and end on DoomZ XII End - Drastrius with DoomZ Command "D.O.O.M.D.U.R.G." (Cannot target with card effects) and Metalsilver Armor (Opponent must target this monster and only this monster).

Ends on 1 omninegate, 1 monsters negate and floodgates opponent out of targeting for combos/destruction effects.

Additionally, normal summon Dragon Buster Destruction Sword and equip with DoomZ XII End - Drastrius to lock opponent out of special summoning.

Pros:

- Low cost (50 points) with large space for handtraps

- Adventure engine as handtrap fodder / insulate plays with omninegates

- Floodgate opponent out of targetting thier own monsters for combos.

Cons

- Kaijus

 

1) Normal/Special Medius the Pure, effect to special Power Patron DoomZ .

2) Effect targeting Medius the Pure to special DoomZ Break - Diactorus and equip. 

3) DoomZ Break - Diactorus destroy Power Patron DoomZ to search DoomZ XII Zero - Drastea 

4) Effect DoomZ XII Zero - Drastea to destroy DoomZ Break - Diactorus  and special summon. Equip DoomZ Command "D.O.O.M.D.U.R.G." DoomZ Break - Diactorus to search Metalsilver Armor .

4.1) Normal summon Dragon Buster Destruction Sword .

5) DoomZ XII Zero - Drastea special into DoomZ XII End - Drastrius and equip Metalsilver Armor .

5.1) DoomZ XII End - Drastrius equip Dragon Buster Destruction Sword .

This is my personal take on Adamancipators. I've grinded hours of DB to get here. Naturia cliff is a magnificent extender that replaces himself, could be a replacement if any of the Meiru engine gets hit.

 

D.D. crow becomes a spot removal in simple gamestates when paired with Chengying, it is very strong.

 

2nd Raptite is mandatory, this is a slower format and grindier games do happen. This deck can recycle with Emeral if you are in a very very slow game.

mini spright engine is an insulator and you can combo with just 3 Monster Zones.

Droll and moonlit turn Raptite into a D.D crow as well, the opponent never sees it coming.

 

Also, tested Dragite, it isn't worth the points. I debated this for a month and I've been testing without it, the deck doesn't need it. We have a ton of ways to close out games. Droll and moonlit chill are super clutch. Whiffing is rare, play smart

This deck is so much fun and has a ton of cool interactions and synergies. Very explosive, very strong, lots of fun, messag me on discord if you have spice or want to talk Spice. #AseTheAviator

deck_excerpt: This is why Premature Burial is better than Monster Reborn
Destiny Draw isn't just for Duel Links anymore...
deck_description:
Deck is untested.

Something I threw together as an 02-11 Yugiboomer who got hyped about the Genesys format. Deck can, in theory, go first or second successfully. Going first you'll want to get your Silent Zeros out at minimum. Going second should focus on trying to OTK, or at least severely cripple, your opponent with Gandora. We run two Dark Magicians to help guarantee an OTK by using Gandora to wipe the field with at least three cards being destroyed/banished. Gandora gets us a 2500+ Silent Magician Zero, the Dark Magician comes back and gets us Secrets of Dark Magic, then we attack for 2500+2500, use Secrets to fuse Gandora and DM into Dark Magician the Dragon Knight, and hit for the last 3000.

deck_name: Budget 60 Card Branded (The Chronicles - The Fallen and The Virtuous Structure Deck x3)
deck_description: It's a fun deck for advanced duelists who love Fusion Summoning.

My local card group allowed us to play with the points and allowed us a 1000 point Genesys Tournament. any suggestions are welcome, and this is as "optimized" as I can make it.

Mass Driver is the fall back, with synchro turbo being the primary. ripping cards from your opponents hand, while also controlling the board.

Bricks will be a bit more common, especially if you draw an all monster hand. 

The main idea with the deck is using Painful Choice and comboing with Graceful chairity, and filtering all your required monsters to the grave.

I wont bother with a combo string due to lengthyness, however with mass driver its good to keep track of what infernity cards are remaining in the deck, grave, banishment, and also remembering if you have a normal summon, or a stygian summon. using launcher to summon out 2 necromancers increases every launcher or mirage summon to a potential 1600 burn each.

with synchro turbo, the primary is to abuse trishula, summoning all 3 and then using all 3 for true king. summoning synchro wolf first makes the board too crowded and bricks your board too easily. try aiming for an endboard with bystial, void, snake-eyes, and true king.

be careful, if mass driver fails, this could set you up for deck-out fairly easily. only use mass driver if you are absolutely sure you have enough for lethal.
(3 launcher in deck or hand, mirage banished for creepy punk target, mirage in hand with normal summon, and mirage in hand as target for stygian.)
**Gentle reminder, ZERO-MAX is for 0 ATK targets. archfiend loses timing, and beetle will destroy your necromancer/mirage,avenger on the field**

with the sideboard, Droll and lock bird hate, along with floodgate hate. skill drain, lose 1 turn, summon limit, anti spell fragrance,droll and lock bird, ash blossom, or any extra deck floodgate.  9 times out of 10, you can burn through enough inturrupts.

deck_excerpt: Plays multiple Field spell related engines to turbo out AFD and use its effects.
deck_description:
The deck aims to set up Eternal Sunshine(ES) and World of Spirits(WoS) turn 1.

The deck has 3 engines:

  • The Regulus based engine can set up both ES and WoS with just Regulus in hand but requires normal summon.
  • The Dragunity engine can set up both with just Remus in hand without normal summoning but requires 2 discards.
  • The Trickstar engine cannot set up alone, but provides a Field spell and a lvl 4. All you need is a tuner.

All 3 engines have some nice interactions with each other. For example, Regulus can ss Candina from hand and the Trickstar cards can set up hand advantage for Dragunity discards.

For the side deck, there are some nice going second cards that have synergy with the deck like Delta of Invitation and Way Where There is a Will. Other than these, I mainly focus on graveyard disruption and s/t destruction as the main deck doesn't have many ways to do this.

I play two test hands here: https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=358315-76368212

These don't have some common plays though. I'll try posting more later.

Please let me know if you have any suggestions. Thanks!

deck_excerpt: Memento  / The Side Deck Remote Duel WCQ Regional Top 8
deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Decks (TCG)

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Jacob Charland

Tournament: The Side Deck Remote Duel WCQ Regional – November 2nd 2025

Placement: Top 8

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

Post 10.27.2025 point list, many Branded duelists despaired seeing how ridiculously expensive some of the Branded cards have become! Branded Fusion's points went from 33 to 40, while most of the Albaz fusions have been slapped with a 10+ point penalty! This makes Branded much weaker, since many sacrifices have to be made just so most of the strategy's engine remains intact since the Branded cards are very point heavy. The decklist very "barebones" lacking key cards such as Titaniklad & Guardian Chimera in the Extra Deck and additional copies of Branded Fusion & Quem in the Main Deck. We couldn't even use the new cards from the Chronicles Structure deck since "The Fallen and Virtuous" and "The Dragon That Devours the Dogma" are all so expensive!

This doesn't mean that Branded isn't viable! In fact, the strategy is still extremely strong in a simplified, lower power level format! Not only is it powerful, the deck is very consistent, hardly bricking with multiple ways to Branded Fusion and several extenders to keep plays going. This deck features an additional Dracotail engine with triple Rahu which is surprisingly free given how incredible that card is!

Otherwise Branded, plays as usual - summoning gigantic fusion boss monsters, immense card advantage, and playing during the infamous "Main Phase 3" (End Phase)! 

After spending about 12 hours deckbuilding, tweaking points and testing in duels, I think I've hit the sweet spot for the ratios of Branded cards with supplimentary engines in the Main, Extra and Side Decks. If you need any explanations with the cards chosen or any other questions feel free to ask in the comments below. :) 

Here is the main combo for GENESYS Branded featuring 1 Aluber, 1 monster and 2 discards: 

1. Normal summon Aluber and activate Aluber's effect to search Branded Fusion. 

2. Activate Branded Fusion to summon Albion, using Albaz and Phryxul from deck. 

3. CL1 Albion to fusion summon Lubellion using Albaz + Aluber, CL2 Phryxul to set from deck Rahu Dracotail. 

4. Activate Lubellion discarding 1 card fusion summon Mirrorjade using Lubellion + Albaz. 

5. Activate Rahu Dracotail to fusion summon Gulamel, using any monster in hand and Dracotail Pan from deck. 

6. Activate Pan's effect to set any Dracotail trap from deck (whatever is relevant to the matchup) and to destroy Albion on field. 

7. During the End Phase, Albion adds to hand Branded Opening. 

8. Activate Branded Opening to summon from deck Quem. 

9. Activate Quem to send to GY Cartesia. 

During your opponent's turn, Quem can summon Cartesia for further fusion plays, Mirrorjade can banish a monster and Dracotail trap with Gulamel's targeted destruction! This is the simplest combo, but stronger endboards can be made if you have the correct hand. 

GLHF Duelists!

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

deck_description:
An attempt to make Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon work in Yugioh Genesys, with a side deck that lets me swap out of the Dragoon/Fusion strategy into an anti-hand trap package, graveyard hate, and/or additional destruction.

Chose to go Dark Magician/Shning Sarcophagus for thematic purposes, but Shining Sarc also allows for an OTK involving Gandora, Dark Magician (either one) and and of the Dark Magician + Dragon fusions through Secrets of Dark Magic.

Note that Dark Magician Girl the Magician's Apprentice's name becomes Dark Magician Girl permanently when special summoned by it's own effect, enabling Magicians' Combination. Unfortunately, Dark Magician the Magician of Black Magic only counts as a Dark Magician while on the field.

deck_excerpt: How to best utilize Ashlan U1000 in the Megalith deck.
deck_description:
I'm updating the Megalith deck I previously made on the website; you can find the main combos I described for the deck at the link below:

 

https://ygoprodeck.com/deck/megalith-october-2025-format-656546

 

Now I'll discuss some changes I made for the TCG format:

 

Today the game's power creep is very high, so to try and compete I made changes to reduce the number of bricks in the main deck and achieve more synergy with the excellent support for Ritual decks that is ASHLAN U1000.

 

I removed Megalith Notrah Plura from the main deck; it's a brick in hand, and modern Yu-Gi-Oh! doesn't tolerate you not being able to play. I'm also using hand traps that can be Normal Summoned to make ASHLAN U1000, which considerably increases the play options after interruptions.

 

In my Extra Deck, I'm using cards useful for all scenarios; there aren't any other Link Monsters that I consider useful, and the XYZ toolbox is very versatile for playing first or second.

 

I've left cards in the Side Deck to improve my going-first strategy.

 

---------------------------------

 

That said, I'll show you in 3 similar combos how you can easily access all 3 Ritual engines in the deck (Megalith, Light Fairy, and Impcantation) with the Megalith engine plus any normal summon:

 

COMBO 1: Unformed + Ophiel + any normal summon

 

Place the continuation of the link on the website duelingbook.com /

replay?id=813757-76414993

 

End Board: ASHLAN U1000 + Drill Driver Vespenato + Anastasis + Portal + Emergence

 

In Hand: Aratron + Phul + Benten + Herald (2 draw, discard 1) In GY: Phuloch and Bethor

 

The cool thing about this combo is that you can do it even if you normal summoned Manju and your opponent negated it with Ash Blossom or Infinite Impermanence, for example.

 

This combo is excellent because you separate the interactions in different places:

 

* You have ASHLAN U1000 on the table to bounce a card, and in the spell/trap zone you have Anastasis to tribute an opponent's monster without targeting.

 

* You have triggers for their effects at different times, one with Phuloch and the other with Aratron, which are ways to Ritual Summon on the opponent's turn.

 

* In addition to Aratron to summon Phul from your hand, you also have Orange Light negate along with Benten in your hand.

 

* There are at least 4 interactions: Bounce ASHLAN U1000, Tribute a monster with Anastasis, Orange Light negate monster, and Benten effect destroy all opponent's cards.

 

I'll show below that you can achieve this endboard with the other Megalith monsters as well:

 

COMBO 2: Unformed + Phuloch + any normal summon

replay?id=813757-76415515

 

COMBO 3: Unformed + Hagith + any normal summon

replay?id=813757-76415810

You can do the same combo if, instead of a level 4 Megalith, you have a level 8 Megalith in your hand along with Unformed. In that case, you use the first Unformed to bring out Hagith, and Hagith adds another Unformed to access Phul from deck and perform the combo normally.

 

With this, the deck became better for playing the traditional TCG, and that's why I'm updating the decklist on the website.

 

-------------------------My thoughts on Megalith in the Genesys format after a month of testing:

 

I was very excited to use Megalith in the Genesys format because the deck doesn't actually need Link monsters to play, and Megalith can be quite competitive in this format, which is a bit more balanced for the deck's power.

 

However, the updated points list no longer allows for optimal use of the deck:

They gave Anastasis 33 points and Manju 1 point, and since Gallant Granite already had 33 points plus Benten's 40 points, it's simply not possible to use all 3 cards at the same time.

 

For me, using Megalith with these cards is indispensable, since the deck no longer has a single combo card, and losing one of its best cards made me abandon the Genesys format and focus solely on seeing how the deck works in the TCG.

 

It has significantly improved with the addition of the new support cards and Ashlan U1000, and I hope you enjoyed what I presented.

deck_excerpt: the 1-card combo for Yummy and Fiendsmith's ideal end board is... a Blackwing?
deck_description:
Blackwing - Steam the Cloak is your 1-stop shop for an ideal Yummy Fiendsmith end board! Here's how:

Normal summon Steam, link him off for Almiraj, triggering his effect to summon a lv1 steam token. Make Cupsy Way with Almiraj and the steam token, then use its effect to add Cupsy and Marshmao, discarding 1 other card. Link Cupsy Way into Snatchy, and place Acroquey form deck (to protect yourself from Nibiru). Next, special summon Marshmao, and make Lollipo Way with it and Snatchy. Lollipo Way will summon back Cupsy Way and Marshmao from GY, which you then use to make Marcher, which in turn summons back Steam.

After this, special summon the Cupsy from your hand, and use its effect to add Surprise, which you'll use to summon back Marshmao from GY, which will then return Surprise to your hand. Synchro summon using Steam as your tuner, and Cupsy and Marshmao as material, to make Armades, Keeper of Boundaries, a LIGHT Fiend. Steam being used as Synchro material will trigger his token-summoning effect again, as it is NOT once per turn. Link him off into Requiem, use its effect to summon Lacrima, which on summon will dump Engraver from deck.

It is CRUCIAL that you wait until after this point to make Herald of the Arc Light (using Marcher and steam token) as it banishes any cards sent from hand or deck to GY, thus ruining your Fiendsmith play.

Use Engraver to shuffle Armades back to summon itself, and equip Requiem form GY to Lacrima so that you can use Lacrima to make Necroquip, and finally overlay Necroquip and Engraver to make D/D/D Wave High King Caesar.

Your end board now consists of: Lollipo★Yummy Way, Herald of the Arc Light, D/D/D Wave High King Caesar, Yummyusment★Acroquey, Yummy☆Surprise set face-down, and 3 more cards in hand!

-cards 1-11 are actual attackers

-cards 12-19 are to summon/aquire attackers

-cards 20-29 are Dark Magician x Dark Magician Girl synergy

-cards 30-32 are to fusion summon from Extra Deck

-cards 33-38 are just to disrupt the opponent

-cards 39-40 are traps that synergize with Dark Magician

In general, it tries to synergize with Dark Magician Girl as it can have powerful benefits. You can summon Dark Magician or similar cards relatively easy due to all the synergy effects.

Open to any suggestion !

deck_excerpt: Genesys OmniHERO: Trading floodgates for hand traps and fun! Good lord, the new Masked HEROs can't come soon enough...
deck_description:
DISCLAIMER: I am an extremely casual player. This deck was built to go head-to-head with other petdecks at Genesys locals, not to top in competitive brackets. I welcome any and all feedback on this list.

Alright, with that out of the way: Here's what I'm cooking.

HERO gets hit pretty hard in Genesys format due to the loss of Xtra HERO Cross Crusader. The lack of consistency for what was already a pretty inconsistent and/or bricky deck means that we need to take a few steps back and think about what we're trying to do here. So far, many of the lists I've seen for HERO in Genesys are just some flavor of turbo Dark Law and Plasma and pass. That is a game plan you can do. However: You use 90 of your allocated points for that (or more realistically 99, if you're playing 3x Elemental HERO Stratos). In addition, that means you can play very few if any pointed hand traps like Snow, Ghost Mourner, Effect Veiler, etc.

Instead, I've tried to build a list that is 1) fun for the person on the other end of the table, and 2) can play handtraps to prevent them from setting up in the first place. By my count, we're playing 23 starters/ways to get to a starter in this deck, which means you're almost never going to open a completely unplayable hand. The 7 handtraps to interrupt your opponent's combo are... okay, but I'll probably change this in the future. We'll revisit that at the end.

Now, onto a few deckbuilding decisions that might raise an eye here:

2x Vision HERO Increase: Even in a 50 card deck, drawing the single garnet is very possible. The risk of that cutting you off the Faris line entirely is, IMO, not worth it. If you draw both... Well, that blows! Notably, a single Increase in the hand isn't the end of the world—It can still be Poly'd or Dark Fusion'd away, or even discard fodder for Evil Assault or Vision HERO Faris.... assuming you have another Increase!

Reinforcement of the Army: 35 points is a lot to spend on a starter. There is a valid argument for cutting this to play more handtraps. My perspective is that it's not only one of the best starters for HERO in the game, it can also be a force multiplier. You have Stratos or Vyon already in hand, and you ROTA into the one-of Solid Soldier to further extend. Still, you could retool this deck to drop ROTA in favor of Fusion Destiny. More thoughts on that at the end.

Elemental HERO Liquid Soldier and Evil HERO Toxic Bubble: Both of these are here to make sure Elemental HERO Absolute Zero are online, but there is definitely an argument for cutting one or both in later builds. I have them in Version 1 of this decklist for the flexibility of Absolute Zero.

Further Development:

Currently, this deck has some awkward cards. Destiny HERO - Malicious and Destiny HERO - Denier  are both really awkward in a world with no link climbing, but you need to play them to have the Destiny HERO - Destroyer Phoenix Enforcer line active. For that reason, there's a world in which you cut the 2x Mali, Denier, and DPE in order to play more hand traps. Those 20 points could go to 2 more Droll and 2 more... something. The more I type this out, the more I like that idea, actually. A handtrap on turn 1 is probably worth more than the possiblity of a DPE on turn 2, and neither Mali nor Denier are starters, so cutting them isn't the worst thing in the world for overall consistency.

Notably, this deck also plays 0 Masked HEROs. If you think floodgates are ontologically evil like me, you understand why this deck isn't built to facilitate Masked HERO Dark Law. It's a shame too, because cards like Masked HERO Acid and Masked HERO Blast can be quite useful as toolbox options. When we rebuild HERO with the new support ( Masked HERO Furnace , Masked HERO Atomic , Masked HERO Dusk Crow , and Elemental HERO Thunder Giant - Voltic Thunder for the uninitiated) in a few months, we'll need to totally redo this list.

And that's it! There's more I could say here but I mean, come on. It's HERO, you know how this works. We've been Faris-ing for Increase for almost 4 years now. I for one cannot wait for Furnace so we can finally consider putting the Increase brick out to pasture. If you have thoughts on this list, feel free to leave a comment or hit me up at callsign_bluejay on Disc. 

Be nice! This was a list made to maximize enjoyment for both people in the duel :]

deck_description:
(YU-GI-OH! DUEL MONSTER)

MAI VALENTINE/KUJAKU MAI ANIME DEFINITIVE DECK - 50 CARDS

Wanted to post a genesys list i have loved playing since it was introduced the spells have changed a bit due to Pot of Extrvagance getting a increase to 10 points but the deck very much didnt change.

Going first the deck is a set up interuption deck with using doombroker to go into either of the traps and getting the other later in the turn. The combo gets even easier if you have magigirl already in rotation due to being able to set up displacment into Intervention to go into using their monster to ritual back out the doombroker plus going into another search with which ever one you sent back to your hand with displaced.

Going 2nd its just dont die to interuption which is semi easy with how easy it is to churn through multiple effects. Being able to go into Fireburster that is basically a towers that can attack twice and deal double damage can easily clear boards without commiting everything. But the deck can allow you to also play the grind game and get to the end thanks to the field spell and other searchers such as origin story.

Hope you enjoy the deck ive been playing it at Genesys locals and been having a ton of fun with it.

deck_excerpt: Invoked, Invocation, Branded, Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon, Despia, Magistus,
deck_description:
Handtraps:

2x Maxx C

2x Fuwalos

2x Meowls

Pure-Draw handtraps, designed to bait; Ash Blossom, Droll & Lock Bird and Called By Grave, allowing your high chance to resolve Branded Fusion succesfully. Also if the opponent doesn't have counter-play, they often just pass-turn with no board, or suboptimal board. Also, each card you draw can be massive for this deck, drawing a branded fusion, lubellion, magical melt down, are all good engines that the opponent will want to stop or more potentlly, drawing into Super Poly for boardbreaking. We want to run as much Engine as possible.

Non-Engine:

1x Called By Grave - Deal with the pesky Ash Blossom or Droll, helps playing going first into draw handtraps.

1x Hex-Light Sealed Fusion - Can be substitued for ANY fusion name. Aleister/Fallen of Albaz/Cartesia/Dark Magician. 

3x Super Poly - Breakers almost any board with this deck.

Normal Summon Aleister, Activate, Chain Superpoly to deny imperm/other forms of interruption, using ED Monster/Light OR Fusion to make your monster with opponents board. Then Activate Invocation, banishing, Aleister + Something from Oppoenents GY to make another monster and get Invocation back to deck & Aleister back to hand.

Same Combo Works With:

NS > Fallen of Albaz with any Albaz ED monster.

NS/SS > Cartesia/Quem/Aluber using Dark/Light enemy monsters.

1x Triple Tactics Talent - Either helps you draw into Super Poly, steals a monster itself, or helps weaken your opponents hand. Good going first or Second.

Bystial Engine:

3x The Bystial Lubellion - Ash Bait. From GY tribute a dragon on field, this helps make the endboard stronger by setting Branded Beast.

1x Bystial Druiswurm - Non-targeting removal option.

1x Bystial Saronir - Best sent with Granguignol, to send sword, regained, opening or lubellion. Depending on what you need.

1x Bystial Magnumhut - Recurcses dragon monsters, including ED monsters, or adds bystial/Albaz in hand.

1x Branded Regained - Adds extra rescursion when you banish which is with a lot of your boss monster effects, it also hurts Maliss. allows extra draws every turn and puts more board pressence by putting Druiswurm or Mangumhut back on field.

1x Branded Beast - Adds an extra pop to your endboard, really good for outing floodgates, helps keep Regained on field.

Invoked Engine:

1x Invocation - Searchable with Aleister, uses enemies GY as fusion material, can summon any monster using in-hand monsters. Adds itself back to deck by adding Aleister back to hand.

1-2x Aleister The Invoker - NS, to add Invocation from deck to hand, can send itself from hand in Battle Phase to increase Fusion monsters ATK by 1000.

3x Magical Meltdown - Searches Aleister. Prevents The activation or cards and effects that include an effect that fusion summoners a fusion monster from being negated [The Activation and NOT the effect] So this doesn't negate ash blossom. But the majority of other negates are useless when this card is on the field. Then your opponent also cannot activate cards or effects on fusion summon. Reducing the amount of times your opponent can interact is so powerful, and when it comes with a search for such a powerful card, its just perfect.

Despia Engine:

2-3x Aluber The Jester of Despia - Main searcher for Branded Fusion, can also search Retribution/Branded in Red/ Regained/Beast. When a fusion leaves the field, you can summon it from GY and negate a monster of the field till the end of the turn, and because it summons itself, you can search again.

3x Branded Opening - Great starter to summon Aluber from deck, also can banish itself from GY to protect fusion monsters from destruction effects, this can protect all Fusion monsters at once.

1x Guiding Quem, The Virtuous - Quem is probably the weakiest card to start with but the best card turn 2/3, considered as both dogmatika and despia, it can be summoned to field by Branded Opening/Titaniklad/Granguignol/Despian Quaeritis when they are removed from the field. Quem allows you to send any card that mentions fallen of albaz from deck to GY, but even better when a monster leaves the ED, summons back a fallen of albaz or 1 monster that mentions at best mirrorjade or another fusion monster.

Branded Engine:

2x Fallen of Albaz - Main name for the deck's fusions. Can be used sometimes to breakboards when summoned. Can catch the opponent off-guard if combined with Magical Meltdown, because they can't negate it.

1x Blazing Cartesia - The best extender for the deck, helps dodge imperm and makes Granguignol. Adds back to hand each turn a fusion is sent to GY.

3x Fusion Deployment - Summons any name to the field, targeting Cartesia/Fallen of Albaz also triggers their effects. However, summoning Aleister, doesn't get the search, but can be good for superpoly, just getting a name and body on field makes for great bait.

2x Branded Fusion - The card to set up the board, summons using Deck, Hand or Field, best sends are Lubellion/Cartesia/Hex-Seal, for dark send Saronir.

1x Branded Retribution - The best Turn 2 Set from Albion, Counter Trap is speed spell 3 meaning its very hard to react to, it negates a special summon and destroys the card, the cost is amazing, putting mirrorjade/albion/lubellion/any other albaz fusion monsters, 2 from the GY OR 1 from field. Then when in the GY it can add Branded Fusion straight back to your hand for amazing follow-up on turn 3.

EXTRA DECK:

0-1x Guardian Chimera - Only good when made with Branded in Red, helps swing the game back in your favour with a pops and draw power.

(Cutable if you prefer not to play Branded in Red and add something else like me, i just think Talents is better).

1x Invoked Mechaba - Uses a light monster either in your GY or opponents. Omni-negate and banish.

1x Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon - Made with Hex-Light and any Dragon monster. Doesn't have onfield POP but has the omni-negate.

1x Invoked Magistus Omega - Made with any ED monster, banishes monsters. When destroyed it summons Lv. 4 Spellcaster (Cartesia/Quem/Aleister) and equips to give 1k ATK.

1x Mirrorjade The Iceblade Dragon - Non-targetting banish. Sends from ED to GY. When removed from field at the end phase destroy all monsters your opponent controls.

1x Rindbrumm The Striking Dragon - Can be made using Mulcharmies/Gurara/Omega. Negates and Spins. Can summon itself or Albaz from GY on your oppoents turn.

1x Invoked Audgoeides - Uses any fusion, pops any monster your opponent controls when summoned or when the opponent special summons. Can banish a fusion monster to gain ATK equal to the banish monster, making it great for beating over towers, getting easily over 4k ATK.

1x Despian Quaeritis - Makes all monsters other than Lv. 8 or higher fusion monsters to 0, giving a safer out to monsters other than too many effects. When leaves the field, summons either Albaz or Despia = Quem/Aluber for extention.

1-0x Starving Venom Fusion Dragon - Any 2 Darks for Super Poly, gains ATK equal to one monster of the field, making it very good for beating over anyone, can copy the effect of any lv 5 or higher and when destroyed it wipes all opponents special summoned monsters.

1x Titaniklad the Ash Dragon - Gains ATK equal to combined levels of monsters used for its summon. Often 12 = 2500+1200=3700. And is unaffected  by ED monsters the turn its summoned, the best card into Dinomorphia. On endphase whilst its in GY you can summon Quem/Albaz.

1x Alba-Lenatus the Abyss Dragon - Best card Vs dragons, you can contact summon using fallen of albaz on field + all dragons on field and it gains attacks up to the number of fusion material used. on endphase add 1 polymerization or fusion normal spell. this includes, Branded Fusion/Fusion Deployment for extection.

1x Granguignol the Dusk Dragon - Uses any light or dark. Sends any Bystial/Garura for combos. when your opponent special summons by monster effect summons either Quem/Quaritis.

1-2x Albion the Branded Dragon - Banishes cards from hand, field, GY to fuse a lv. 8 or lower fusion. When in GY it sets a branded spell/trap. Can be tributed for Lubellion.

1x Lubellion the Searing Dragon - Puts cards from field, GY or banished back into the deck to fusion.

1x Garura Wings of Resonant Life - Super Poly target to out most decks, when sent to GY draws a card.

Combos:

Magical Meltdown > Adds Aleister The Invoker > NS > Activate > Adds Invocation

Branded Fusion > Sending (Lubellion for Pure Bystial Branded, Hex-Light for Dragoon, Cartesia For Granguional)

deck_excerpt: KITKALLOS IS BACK!!! (This time in GENESYS).
deck_description:
Kitkallos, you're as beautiful as the day that we've lost you... 🥹

Although severly limited by the GENESYS points list with Scheiren and Kitkallos costing a whopping FIFTY POINTS apiece, (thus taking up this deck's entire points budget), Tearlaments is still an extremely powerful deck! Don't believe me? Check out my Youtube video below to see the deck in action! 

Experience the familiar dopamine high as you mill your entire deck to the graveyard, plussing a bazillion times like no tomorrow as you create an unbreakable board with the likes of Tearlaments Rulkallos (Summon negate), Tearlaments Cryme (Omni-negate shuffle), Tearlaments Sulliek (Monster negate), and Tearlaments Kaleidoheart (Target shuffle).

This strategy also has access to a large synchro suite due to millable tuners as well as the Lightsworn engine! Genex Return Zero (Monster negate destroy for each attribute), Draco Berserker of the Tenyi (Monster banish), Juraishin (Monster of spell field wide destruction), Chengying (Monster banish) and Wolfrayet (Shuffle all monsters your opponent controls). 

For the counterattack, Tearlaments can field fearsome gigantic beatsticks like Liberator Eto (4000ATK) and Alba System (Can attack every monster once and its 4500ATK)! 

The main weakness of this deck is bricking and getting unlucky with mills. However, once the milling gets going, almost nothing stops Tearlaments from winning the game, especially in the lower power fomat of GENESYS! The combination of Scheiren, Kitkallos, TearKash and Scream mill 14 cards! The Lightsworn cards can also mill quite a bit as well, with both Minervas milling 7 cards and Weiss milling 2! It's often that after you end your turn, you may have only about 5-10 cards left in deck due to how much you mill, search and draw! 

Tearlaments in GENESYS functions as usual, milling as much as possible with the combined effort of the Tearlaments and Lightsworn cards. Make impenetrable boards going first and power through everything with immense amounts of milling going second with pure engine! Mill mill mill your way to victory!

And remember... TIARAMENTS STRONGEST~

(Shoutout to Lithium2300's Tearlament decklist and Youtube video for inspiring this deck!)

GLHF Duelists!

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!
Deck featruing old, fun Yu-Gi-Oh! combos. Personal Favorite cards, & quick anime strategies!

deck_excerpt: I know, but I promise try it out is golden
deck_description: I know, but I promise try it out is golden

This deck aims to avoid Droll & Lock Bird until at least VALCan Booster is on field.Hence the use of Girsu & O-Lion to put 2 machines on field.
Girsu dumps Crown, for Galatea-I to add it back from GY (avoiding Droll).
Girsu puts a token on the opponent's side of the field, preventing further Impulses, Purge, Impermanence, also enabling Thrust to add Stage Landing.
Galatea-I can discard Cannon or Blade if opening with them, making them not bricks anymore and it can also discard O-Lion for another body on field.
You can also play under Droll (make sure to guarantee Funk Dock on field), getting to Shepherd and setting Last Stand: summon Blade on Shepherd arrow, dump Driller; then use Blade, use Funk Dock to summon Cutter; then, after using Cutter, return Blade and Cutter to summon Driller with Shepherd. This way you have and easy loop setup with Funk Dock + Shepherd + Last Stand as Shepherd can set Last Stand again next turn.
This guarantee you and easy 3 interruptions every turn.

deck_description: Fusion and synchro deck with some pretty good OTK potential going second.
Chan The Man Realmente Ganó un Juego Regional...¿Monarca?

(YU-GI-OH! DUEL MONSTER)

WEEVIL UNDERWOOD/INSECTOR HAGA ANIME DEFINITIVE DECK - 50 CARDS



Sometime after the events of DM!

This is my perfected version of Paleozoic - with a dracotail package of 5 cards, the soldier dragon + laundry package as well as 2 sol now that he can't be sent to the GY by Sprind

I don't think there is anything here that could be cut unless you want to switch out Dogmatika Punishment for the third Canadia and another trap I'm running at 2 like IDP, or a third Time Tearing potentially. I wanted 3 Mirage, but really needed the 3rd Karma Cannon and wouldnt play Rollback or Trap Holic at less than 3, and Zeus is essential too so this is how I found it worked best.  There are 2 draw traps in Balance of Judgment, which can be rotated out for Hope for Escape when going first to pair with Rollback. 

Trap Holic + Mirage of Nightmare is just a game winning swing honestly, draw 4, pop Mirage with Trap Holic, chain a paleo etc

The side deck is just a guesstimate really, I like Dogmatika Punishment in main with Ulti Slayer in side with various targets - I did have Vallon here too but as I'm trying the Waking the dragons I thought that this could work well with the big towers guy. You can also use waking the dragon into Opabinia to turn on your in hand Paleos you draw off Mirage which is nice. 

I've played paleo for a couple of years now and its always a fun deck. Just don't lose to time I guess. Dragon Gate helps with that to set up a big final OTK, and the Mosquito + Sol play can reverse OTK people in their battle phase if you save a paleo to summon in BP 

 

The only other card I wanted to try was the new DOOD cont trap that mills 10, but it seems a bit win more here and hard to actually find from the deck

deck_description:
Any kind of pendulum decks based on magicians/spellcasters is gonna be great. (P)Endymion is one of my favorite variants for its ability to swarm the field with non-HOPT negates and annoyances.

 

Radiant Typhoon just gives that little kick it was missing to actually survive in the current meta!

 

A new version might come soon as the Dark Magician support is expected to be released very shortly, which brings the deck to even greater heights.

 

"Pend best deck baby let's gooooooooo" - Trif, aka THE Pend God
